  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Tuck into a delicious daily buffet breakfast, with hot and cold options on offer. If you book half board, enjoy a three-course evening meal (choose from the à la carte menu) and impressive views in the award-winning <strong>Scala Restaurant</strong>. Recipes celebrating the tastes of southern Switzerland, Italy, France and Greece are crafted using fresh and quality ingredients.</p>
<p>The <strong>Louis Bar</strong> is a Lucerne hotspot for drinks and live music. It has the most extensive whisky collection in the whole of Switzerland, including over 130 classic Scottish malts. Enjoy regular live jazz and funk &amp; soul.</p>
<p><strong>Hemmingway's Rum &amp; Cigar Lounge</strong> contains the largest selection of rums in Switzerland, with over 60 from Central and South America. The bar pays homage to famous writer Ernest Hemingway who wrote about the hotel in his 1936 short story, The Capital of the World. Please be aware that this is a smoker's bar, with air filters to remove smoke particles.</p>
<p><strong>Montana Beach Club</strong> is a bar and terrace serving drinks and cocktails overlooking Lake Lucerne. There are comfy lounge seats, umbrellas, and palm trees to set the beach bar scene.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
